<h2>Engaging Culturally Diverse Families for Student Success</h2>
<p>A student with a disability is first, and foremost, a student who is a member of the school community. In order for parents of students with disabilities to be meaningfully involved as a member of their child&rsquo;s Individualized Education Program team, they first need to feel welcomed and valued. They must also understand how &ldquo;regular education&rdquo; works. </p>
<p>When schools are intentional and proactive in using culturally-competent strategies to provide information and support to families who are from diverse cultures or speak another language, they pave the way for meaningful family engagement, and better outcomes for students. </p>
